verbose_text: In the therapeutic range of UFH versus anti-Xa (0.3-0.7 IU/mL), 91% of samples were accurately categorized by ratio CKH.R/CK.R, 90% by ratio CK.R/CKH.R, and 92% by DeltaCK.R - CKH.R, with a PPV of 88% for DeltaCK.R - CKH.R and ratio CK.R/CKH.R, and 89% for ratio CKH.R/CK.R (XREF_TABLE), demonstrating that blood samples could be accurately classified according to clinically relevant levels of UFH.
